-- German Stocks Drop as Adidas, Commerzbank Shares Retreat
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   M o r g a n
-- 2012-09-11T08:26:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-11/german-stocks-drop-led-by-heidelbergcement-commerzbank-adidas.html
German stocks declined as investors
awaited tomorrow’s verdict from the country’s top constitutional
court on participation in the European Stability Mechanism, the
region’s permanent bailout fund.  The benchmark DAX Index dropped 0.3 percent to 7,191.29 at
10:23 a.m. in  Frankfurt . The broader HDAX fell 0.4 percent.
HeidelbergCement AG, Commerzbank AG and Adidas AG led losses,
each sliding at least 2 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
